4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR SETBACKS FOR WIND TURBINE
5 GENERATORS; ESTABLISHING A WIND TURBINE GENERATOR DEICING STANDARD; AMENDING
6 SECTION 70-17-406, MCA; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Required setback for wind turbine generators. (1) After [the effective
11 date of this act], a wind turbine generator built pursuant to a wind energy agreement as described in 70-17-406
12 may not be constructed if the wind turbine tower is 500 feet or more in height, as measured from the natural
13 ground level at the base of the tower to the tip of the turbine rotor blade, and if the base of the tower is located
14 at a distance of less than
15 1,500 feet from an occupied residence that is subject to a wind energy agreement as described in 70-
16 17-406 with the owner of the wind turbine generator, unless the setback distance is approved by the owner of
17 the real property.
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Wind turbine generator deicing -- requirement. A wind turbine
20 generator constructed after [the effective date of this act] that is 500 feet or more in height, as measured from
21 the natural ground level at the base of the tower to the tip of the turbine rotor blade, and is located within a
22 distance of 2,500 feet from an occupied residence in accordance with [section 1] may not exceed 10% of the
23 maximum turbine rotor blade speed during the turbine rotor blade deicing process, unless the rotor blade speed
24 is approved by the owner of the real property.
25
26 Section 3. Section 70-17-406, MCA, is amended to read:
27 "70-17-406. Wind energy agreement -- contents and requirements -- notarization -- fee. (1) A
28 wind energy agreement executed after April 21, 2011 January 1, 2026, must contain but is not limited to:
